-- China Stocks: Agricultural Bank, Hainan Airlines, Poly, Vanke,
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-09T08:28:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/changan-auto-china-shenhua-energy-western-mining-china-equity-preview.html
The  Shanghai Composite Index , which
tracks the bigger of China’s stock exchanges, fell 0.8 percent
to 3,134.99 at the 3 p.m. local time close. The  CSI 300 Index 
declined 0.7 percent to 3,523.95.  Banks: A  gauge  tracking financial companies slumped 2.1
percent, the most among the CSI 300’s 10 industry groups.
Agricultural Bank of China Ltd. (601288 CH) lost 2.1 percent to
2.83 yuan.  Bank of Communications Co.  (601328 CH) dropped 1.7
percent to 6.26 yuan.  China will force banks to hold more foreign exchange and
strengthen auditing of overseas fund raising as part of efforts
to crack down on hot-money inflows.  Property developers: Chinese government departments are
drafting rules to allow authorities to intervene in home prices,
the Securities Times reported today, citing unidentified people.  Local governments may be given the power to limit selling
prices of homes and profits developers take, according to the
Shenzhen-based newspaper.  China Vanke Co.  (000002 CH), the nation’s largest publicly
traded developer by market value, fell 4 percent to 9.50 yuan,
the most since Oct. 20.  Poly Real Estate Group Co.  (600048 CH),
the second biggest developer, lost 4.1 percent to 14.47 yuan.  Hainan-related stocks surged after the Shanghai Securities
News reported the southern province may start duty-free shopping
from Jan. 1.  Hainan Airlines Co.  (600221 CH) gained by the maximum 10
percent to 10.23 yuan. Hainan Expressway Co. (000886 CH) also
surged by the daily limit to 7.11 yuan, as did Hainan Zhenghe
Industrial Group Co. (600759 CH) to 6.55 yuan.  The duty-free zones will include Sanya and Haikou,
according to the report, which cited an unidentified person.  Guizhou Tyre Co.  (000589 CH): The tire maker said it
received conditional approval from the China Securities
Regulatory Commission for a rights offer. The stock jumped 2
percent to 15.02 yuan, the highest since April 26.  Tianjin FAW Xiali Automobile Co.  (000927 CH): The company
said October vehicle sales were 24,849 units, up from 16,080 a
year earlier. The stock rose 2.1 percent to 10.40 yuan, the
highest since March 9.  Western Mining Co.  (601168 CH): China’s fourth-largest
maker of zinc concentrate said its parent has bought an 80
percent stake in a zinc and lead mining company for 2.2 billion
yuan. The stock advanced 6.4 percent to 20.54 yuan, the highest
since June 2008.  -- Zhang Shidong . Editor:  Allen Wan   To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
